<i>adverb</i>: 한낱 [한낟], 한갓 [한갇], 비단 [비단], 다만 [다ː만], 겨우 [겨우] <i>determiner</i>: 단 [단] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>한낱 [한낟]</dt><br>
<dd>only; just; merely; nothing but</dd><br>
<dd>아무리 한다고 해야 대단한 것 없이 다만.</dd><br>
<dd>Only to such an extent without something great even if one tries hard.</dd><br>
<dt>한갓 [한갇]</dt><br>
<dd>just; only; merely</dd><br>
<dd>아무리 좋거나 크게 보려고 해도 겨우.</dd><br>
<dd>Nothing more than something even if one tries to think of it as good or large.</dd><br>
<dt>비단 [비단]</dt><br>
<dd>simply; merely</dd><br>
<dd>여럿 가운데 오직.</dd><br>
<dd>Only something among many.</dd><br>
<dt>다만 [다ː만]</dt><br>
<dd>1. merely</dd><br>
<dd>다른 것이 아니라 오로지.</dd><br>
<dd>Only, not others.</dd><br>
<dd>2. just</dd><br>
<dd>그 정도라도.</dd><br>
<dd>Only to such an extent.</dd><br>
<dd>3. but</dd><br>
<dd>앞에 말한 내용과 다른 조건이나 예외가 있을 때 뒤 문장의 시작 부분에 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An adverb used at the beginning of a sentence, when it includes an exception or condition different from the content of the preceding sentence.</dd><br>
<dt>겨우 [겨우]</dt><br>
<dd>1. with difficulty</dd><br>
<dd>아주 힘들게.</dd><br>
<dd>With much effort.</dd><br>
<dd>2. only; merely</dd><br>
<dd>다해야 고작.</dd><br>
<dd>At a minimum.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>determiner</i><br>
<dt>단 [단]</dt><br>
<dd>just; merely; simply</dd><br>
<dd>오직 그 수량뿐임을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A word that indicates there is only the amount of something.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>